</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<taxonomicName class="Pucciniomycetes" genus="Uredo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Uredo aureospora" order="Pucciniales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="aureospora">Uredo aureospora</taxonomicName>
1960 has priority but it cannot be moved to 
<taxonomicName class="Pucciniomycetes" genus="Hemileia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hemileia" order="Pucciniales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">Hemileia</taxonomicName>
because that name already exists in the genus. For this reason the next oldest name 
<taxonomicName class="Pucciniomycetes" genus="Hemileia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hemileia aureospora" order="Pucciniales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="aureospora">Hemileia aureospora</taxonomicName>
is the accepted scientific name for this species of which 
<taxonomicName class="Pucciniomycetes" genus="Uredo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Uredo aureospora" order="Pucciniales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="aureospora">Uredo aureospora</taxonomicName>
is a taxonomic synonym. Although the name 
<taxonomicName class="Pucciniomycetes" genus="Hemileia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hemileia aureospora" order="Pucciniales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="aureospora">Hemileia aureospora</taxonomicName>
was previously considered to be not validly published because the type specimen lacked teliospores and thus violated Article 59 of the now outdated International Code of Botanical Nomenclature (ICBN) (
<bibRefCitation pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Stafleu et al. 1972</bibRefCitation>
), the new ICN allows this name to be used.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
